properties.headline: Special Weather Statement issued January 7 at 11:53PM MST by NWS Riverton WY
properties.description:
* WHAT...Southwest winds 25 to 35 mph with gusts to 50 to 55 mph.
Occasional gusts to 60 to 65 mph are possible in favored areas
like Wyoming Boulevard south of Casper.

* WHERE...Along the Highway 287 corridor from Beaver Rim to
Sweetwater Station and Jeffrey City, along the Highway 220
corridor from Alcova to Casper and Wyoming Boulevard south of
Casper.

* WHEN...Through 6 pm today.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Anyone traveling along Highway 20/26, 220,
287 and Interstate 25 on Tuesday should anticipate sudden
strong cross winds.

NWSheadline: One more night and day of strong winds
